## 1 · Architectural decomposition of Hermes Agent

### 1.1 Repository topology

The Hermes core is one Python orchestration class — `AIAgent` in [`run_agent.py`](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent) — shared verbatim by every entry point (CLI, TUI, gateway, ACP server, cron, batch runner). Around it sit the following directories ([AGENTS.md](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/blob/main/AGENTS.md), [architecture.md](https://github.com/mudrii/hermes-agent-docs/blob/main/architecture.md)):

| Path | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `run_agent.py` | `AIAgent` core loop (~60 constructor parameters; single hot path) |
| `agent/transports/` | `ProviderTransport` ABC + `AnthropicTransport`, `ChatCompletionsTransport`, `ResponsesApiTransport`, `BedrockTransport` (v0.11.0) |
| `agent/prompt_builder.py` | `load_soul_md()`, `build_skills_system_prompt()`, `build_context_files_prompt()` |
| `agent/context_compressor.py` | `ContextCompressor` — adaptive compaction, anti-thrashing |
| `agent/auxiliary_client.py` | `call_llm()` / `async_call_llm()` central router for nine auxiliary tasks |
| `agent/credential_pool.py` | Multi-credential rotation, exhaustion handling, OAuth refresh |
| `agent/smart_model_routing.py` | Cheap-vs-strong route picker |
| `hermes_state.py` | `SessionDB` — SQLite WAL, schema v6, FTS5 + trigram virtual tables |
| `gateway/` | 20-platform gateway runner; per-platform adapter classes |
| `gateway/platforms/` | One file per platform; all subclass `BasePlatformAdapter` |
| `tools/` | 49 tool implementations including `skill_manage`, `memory`, `session_search`, `kanban_*` |
| `tools/kanban_tools.py` | Worker-side board tools; gated by env `HERMES_KANBAN_TASK` |
| `plugins/kanban/` | Dispatcher long-loop, dashboard, systemd unit |
| `plugins/memory/{honcho,mem0,supermemory,hindsight,holographic,retaindb,byterover,openviking}/` | Pluggable memory providers |
| `plugins/context_engine/` | Pluggable context-compaction engines |
| `honcho_integration/` | Dialectic user modeling (two-layer base + dialectic) |
| `cron/` | 60-second tick scheduler; jobs include Autonomous Curator |
| `acp_adapter/entry.py` | `hermes-acp` editor server (Zed, VS Code, JetBrains) |
| `skills/` (bundled), `~/.hermes/skills/` (runtime) | Procedural memory store |
| `optional-skills/migration/openclaw-migration/` | The `hermes claw migrate` helper |

The contract is **plugin-clean**: core never imports plugin internals; plugins reach core only through `hermes/plugin-sdk/*`. mindX should preserve this contract when porting — the BDI core stays plugin-agnostic, Hermes-style behaviors enter as MASTERMIND-managed plugins. License is **MIT** ([LICENSE](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/blob/main/LICENSE)).

### 1.2 Twenty-plus messaging gateway platforms

The gateway is the largest single porting surface in Hermes and the one most relevant to mindX's existing user-touchpoints. All adapters inherit `BasePlatformAdapter` (`gateway/platforms/base.py`) and implement `connect()`, `disconnect()`, `send()`, `get_chat_info()`. Confirmed in v0.13.0: Telegram, Discord, Slack, WhatsApp, Signal, SMS (Twilio), Mattermost, Matrix (matrix-nio, E2EE), Webhook (HMAC), Email (IMAP/SMTP), Home Assistant, Feishu/Lark, WeCom, Weixin, BlueBubbles iMessage, QQ Bot, Yuanbao, DingTalk, Microsoft Teams (plugin), **Google Chat (the 20th platform shipped in Tenacity)**, plus LINE on `main` post-release. An `api_server.py` adapter exposes an OpenAI-compatible `/v1/chat/completions` with `X-Hermes-Session-Id` continuity. Each platform has a paired `hermes-<platform>` toolset for per-platform tool gating.

### 1.3 TUI / CLI / ACP triplet

The classic CLI (`cli.py`, prompt_toolkit) coexists with a React/Ink TUI launched via `hermes --tui`, which fronts a Python JSON-RPC `tui_gateway` process that talks to the same `AIAgent`. The `hermes-acp` console entry (under `acp_adapter/entry.py`) gives Zed, VS Code, and JetBrains an Agent Client Protocol surface, with `/steer` and `/queue` for in-flight redirection (v0.13.0) and atomic session persistence via PR [#20279](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/20279).

