## 5 · Self-healing patterns

### 5.1 v0.13.0 Tenacity: the operational substrate

The release notes ([RELEASE_v0.13.0.md](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/blob/main/RELEASE_v0.13.0.md)) describe the theme as *"Hermes Agent now finishes what it starts."* Five primitives ship together:

1. **Kanban durable multi-agent board** ([plugins/kanban/](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent), [Kanban user guide](https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/docs/user-guide/features/kanban)) — SQLite at `~/.hermes/kanban.db`, six columns (Triage, Todo, Ready, In progress, Blocked, Done), three workspace kinds (`scratch`, `dir:<absolute>`, `worktree`). Dispatcher tick default 60 s (`kanban.dispatch_interval_seconds`). Workers spawned as full OS processes with `HERMES_KANBAN_TASK=<id>` and `HERMES_KANBAN_BOARD=<slug>` pinned so they cannot see other boards. CLI: [`hermes_cli/kanban.py`](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent) — `init, create, list, show, assign, link, unlink, comment, complete, block, unblock, archive, tail, watch, stats, runs, log, assignees, heartbeat, notify-*, dispatch, daemon, gc`. Worker schema: [`tools/kanban_tools.py`](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent) — `kanban_show, kanban_complete, kanban_block, kanban_heartbeat, kanban_comment, kanban_create, kanban_link, kanban_unblock`. Dashboard at `http://127.0.0.1:9119`; systemd unit `plugins/kanban/systemd/hermes-kanban-dispatcher.service`.
2. **Heartbeat monitoring** — long-running workers emit `kanban_heartbeat` periodically; the dispatcher reclaims tasks whose heartbeat goes stale past the claim TTL.
3. **Zombie detection** — three triggers: PID gone before TTL expires; worker exited without `kanban_complete`/`kanban_block` ([PR #21214](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/21214)); darwin defunct-child detection ([#20188](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/20188)). Recovery: reclaim back to `ready` or auto-block. A **circuit breaker auto-blocks after ~5 consecutive spawn failures** to prevent infinite spin loops. The new **diagnostics engine for task distress signals** ([#20332](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/20332)) unifies these.
4. **Hallucination recovery gate** ([PR #20232](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/20232), closes [#20017](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/issues/20017)) — invoked at task completion, specifically on `kanban_complete()` claims. The gate "verifies completion claims before tasks close, catching workers that report 'done' on patches that never landed" ([AlphaSignal](https://alphasignalai.substack.com/p/you-should-install-hermes-agent-this)). Pairs with post-write delta lint on `write_file` and `patch` for Python/JSON/YAML/TOML ([#20191](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/20191)) plus per-task `max_retries` ([#21330](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/21330)). The **exact detection technique** is not documented verbatim; from PR context the likely mechanism is **post-condition verification of claimed changes against actual filesystem/tool-call evidence** plus syntactic lint on declared modified files. Failed gate → task returns to the board with gate findings appended as a comment, so the next worker (via `build_worker_context`) sees prior attempt + reason and does not blindly redo the same path. This is the single most novel feature in Tenacity.
5. **Per-task retries with budget**, **auto-block on incomplete worker exit**, and **`no_agent` cron watchdog mode**.

A turn-level hallucination problem ([issue #5563](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/issues/5563)) at 700 K+ token contexts is **separate** from the kanban gate — handled by context compression and `/compress`, not by the gate.

### 5.2 Session repair

Hermes does not ship a function literally named `repairSessionFileIfNeeded`. The equivalents:

- **Atomic session persistence** — [PR #20279](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/20279) (atomic ACP persistence via `replace_messages`), [PR #20296](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/20296) (preserve assistant reasoning metadata).
- **Gateway auto-resume after restart** — [PR #21192](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/21192).
- **JSONL fallback** — when `state.db` cannot open, the gateway falls back to writing JSONL transcripts at `~/.hermes/sessions/` and logs a warning ([issue #13029](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/issues/13029)). JSONL on disk is the canonical recovery source.
- **Atomic restart markers + Windows runtime-lock offset** — [PR #18179](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/18179).
- **Preserve pending update prompts across restarts** — [PR #20160](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/20160).
- **TUI compression continuation guard** for ghost sessions with incomplete metadata (release notes #20001).

So Hermes' posture is **prevention via atomic writes + JSONL fallback**, not on-startup scan-and-repair. mindX should adopt both: BEGIN IMMEDIATE + retry-with-jitter + WAL checkpointing for the SQLite tier, JSONL transcripts as the recoverable ground truth.

### 5.3 Error recovery, rollback, Checkpoints v2

- **Slash command `/rollback`** in both CLI and gateway ([slash-commands.md](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/blob/main/website/docs/reference/slash-commands.md)).
- **Checkpoints v2** ([PR #20709](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/20709)) — single shared shadow git repo at `~/.hermes/checkpoints/store/`; auto-snapshots before destructive terminal commands (`rm`, `rmdir`, `cp`, `install`, `mv`, `sed -i`, `truncate`, `dd`, `shred`, output redirects `>`, `git reset/clean/checkout`); at most one checkpoint per directory per turn. **`/rollback` semantics**: verifies the target commit exists; takes a pre-rollback snapshot (so you can undo the undo); restores tracked files; **undoes the last conversation turn so the agent's context matches the restored filesystem state** — this is the turn-level transactionality. Opt-in (`checkpoints.enabled: false`) by default in v2.
- **`/snapshot create|restore|prune|list`** — config/state snapshots, separate from filesystem.
- **Memory-write transaction semantics** — SQLite session store uses `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` plus retry loop with jittered backoff (20–150 ms, up to 15 retries) per [session-storage docs](https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/docs/developer-guide/session-storage). Periodic WAL checkpoints every 50 successful writes (PASSIVE mode). [Hindsight memory plugin](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent) has dedupe-on-append for `update_mode='append'` ([PR #20222](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/20222)).

### 5.4 Authentication self-healing

`agent/credential_pool.py` is the heart. Multi-credential pool with four rotation strategies; on 429/exhaustion, mark and rotate. CLI sync from `~/.codex/auth.json`, `~/.claude/.credentials.json`. TOCTOU hardening in v0.13.0: [`hermes_cli/auth.py`](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent) ([PR #21194](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/21194)), MCP OAuth ([PR #21176](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/21176)). `auth.json` restored with 0600 perms ([PR #19699](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/19699)). Refresh skew via `CODEX_ACCESS_TOKEN_REFRESH_SKEW_SECONDS`; `DEFAULT_AGENT_KEY_MIN_TTL_SECONDS` gates re-issuance. Open bugs to know about: [issue #15099](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/issues/15099) (Nous refresh-token rotation not persisting across 4 profiles), [issue #7230](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/issues/7230) (`fallback_model` not triggered when primary auth fails at credential resolution). Auth healing is **good but not bulletproof**.

### 5.5 Memory corruption detection

Hermes uses SQLite + FTS5 with trigger-driven index sync. There is **no automatic `PRAGMA integrity_check` on startup** and **no auto-rebuild of the FTS5 index**. Recovery is manual: `sqlite3 state.db "PRAGMA integrity_check"` → `.dump` → filter → rebuild FTS via `INSERT INTO messages_fts(messages_fts) VALUES('rebuild');`. If SQLite cannot open at all (e.g., FTS5 module missing — [issue #13029](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/issues/13029)), the gateway falls back to JSONL-only transcripts and logs a warning. Auto-prune `VACUUM` runs after row deletion. **mindX should add explicit startup integrity check** — this is one of the few places where mindX can genuinely improve on Hermes.

### 5.6 Graceful degradation

Three triggers for fallback: timeout, model-unavailable, provider error. PR [#19665](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/19665) triggers fallback on timeout alongside model-unavailable. `HERMES_STREAM_STALE_TIMEOUT` (default 180 s, scaled to 240–300 s for large context) classifies hangs as `FailoverReason.timeout`. Auxiliary fallback routes compression, vision, title-gen, session_search through separate providers. The OPENROUTER_API_KEY-missing bug (release note #20982) was fixed in v0.13.0 — fallback providers now correctly honored when the primary key is absent.

