## 9 · Security posture for the integration

CVE-2026-7113 is real and instructive. Component: `gateway/platforms/webhook.py`. Class: Improper Authentication, CWE-287. Affected version: **hermes-agent v0.8.0 (2026.4.8) only**. CVSS 3.x 5.6 MEDIUM (high attack complexity — operator must have explicitly configured `INSECURE_NO_AUTH`). Published 27 April 2026 ([NVD](https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-7113), [Shenlong CVE Intel](https://cve.imfht.com/intel/589978?lang=en)). Root issue documented in [#6440](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/issues/6440). Fix: reject `INSECURE_NO_AUTH` at startup unless `HERMES_ALLOW_INSECURE_WEBHOOKS=1` is set, plus runtime warning. The pattern for mindX: **any "no auth" toggle must require an explicit environment-variable acknowledgement and emit a startup warning every boot**.

Earlier security history worth absorbing: the v0.8.0 hardening wave (path traversal in checkpoint manager, shell injection in sandbox writes, SSRF redirect guards in Slack image uploads, Twilio webhook signature validation, API server auth enforcement, git argument injection prevention, approval-button authorization — PRs [#7933](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/7933), [#7944](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/7944), [#7940](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/7940), [#7151](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/7151), [#7156](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/7156)); the v0.13.0 wave (8 P0 closures including redaction-by-default, Discord guild-scoped role allowlists, WhatsApp stranger-reject, TOCTOU patches on `hermes_cli/auth.py` and MCP OAuth, browser cloud-metadata SSRF floor, `hermes debug share` redaction at upload, cron prompt-injection scan of skill content — see [RELEASE_v0.13.0.md](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/blob/main/RELEASE_v0.13.0.md)). The community audit ([#7826](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/issues/7826)) found "4 Critical, 9 High severity findings in default configuration" — no malware, but ALLOW-ALL defaults. **mindX should ship with DENY-ALL defaults and require explicit allow-list activation per surface.**

The OpenClaw side is materially worse: 9 CVEs in 4 days in March 2026 (one CVSS 9.9), CVE-2026-25253 at CVSS 8.8, and a Koi Security audit finding **341 malicious entries in 2,857 ClawHub skills** (12 % malware rate; 335 tied to one campaign). For mindX, this means: do **not** auto-install community skills; treat the ClawHub registry as untrusted input; mirror Hermes' agent-side scanner that screens new skills for data exfiltration, prompt injection, destructive commands, and supply-chain signals before persisting them.

