## 11 · Foundry and mainnet integration notes

The OpenAgents track is 0G-aligned, so mindX integration with the 0G stack ([0G Storage / DA / Compute / Chain](https://ethglobal.com/events/openagents/prizes)) is the natural deployment path. Concrete posture:

- **Skill files live on 0G Storage.** SKILL.md is content-addressable; the manifest hash is registered on 0G Chain so the MASTERMIND can verify a skill before loading. This addresses the OpenClaw ClawHub-malware vector at the storage layer.
- **Session FTS5 + WAL stays local** (latency-sensitive); periodic snapshot ships to 0G DA for durable recovery. JSONL transcripts as the canonical fallback are 0G-Storage-friendly.
- **iNFT (ERC-7857) identity binding for SOUL.md.** Each mindX profile gets a non-transferable identity NFT carrying the SOUL.md hash plus the 768-dim consciousness vector commitment. Soul updates require a gated on-chain transaction; this gives Soul-tier immutability cryptographic teeth.
- **Sealed inference via 0G Compute for production-sensitive turns** — particularly relevant for any DELTAVERSE / BANKON financial agents, where MEV resistance and front-running mitigation matter. Hermes' provider-agnostic transport ABC ports cleanly: add a `ZeroGSealedTransport` next to `AnthropicTransport`/`BedrockTransport`.
- **Foundry-side**: the iNFT identity contract, a skill manifest registry, and a treasury contract for self-paying inference. Pattern reference is CLAWD's wallet-on-Base treasury model, minus the "no PR review" choice — mindX commits should still be human-gated until the BDI Belief layer has been stress-tested in adversarial conditions.

The ETHGlobal track is **strictly for framework-level work**, and the mindX submission fits as "self-evolving agent framework that autonomously generates/tests/integrates new skills/tools using persistent 0G Storage memory" — bullet two of the [OpenAgents prize page](https://ethglobal.com/events/openagents/prizes) verbatim.

